&lt;p&gt;In a Linux system, when the Spring Boot application is started with the &lt;code&gt;java -jar&lt;/code&gt; command, a tomcat (or undertow) will be generated in the /tmp directory of the operating system. The uploaded file must first be converted into a temporary file and saved in this folder. Because the files in the temporary /tmp directory are not used for a long time (10 days), they will be automatically deleted by the system mechanism. Therefore, if the system has not used the temporary folder for a long time, it may cause the above problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>